verses.text: Now it came to pass upon a day , that Jonathan the son of Saul said unto the young man that bare his armour , Come , and let us go over to the Philistines’ garrison , that \add is\add* on the other side. But he told not his father.\f + \fr 14.1 \ft it came…: or, there was a day\f*
And Saul tarried in the uttermost part of Gibeah under a pomegranate tree which \add is\add* in Migron : and the people that \add were\add* with him \add were\add* about six hundred men ;

And Ahiah , the son of Ahitub , I-chabod’s brother , the son of Phinehas , the son of Eli , the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* priest in Shiloh , wearing an ephod. And the people knew not that Jonathan was gone.\f + \fr 14.3 \ft Ahiah: called Ahimelech\f* \p

¶ And between the passages , by which Jonathan sought to go over unto the Philistines’ garrison , \add there was\add* a sharp rock on the one side , and a sharp rock on the other side : and the name of the one \add was\add* Bozez , and the name of the other Seneh.
The forefront of the one \add was\add* situate northward over against Michmash , and the other southward over against Gibeah.\f + \fr 14.5 \ft forefront: Heb. tooth\f*

And Jonathan said to the young man that bare his armour , Come , and let us go over unto the garrison of these uncircumcised : it may be that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* will work for us: for \add there is\add* no restraint to the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* to save by many or by few.
And his armourbearer said unto him, Do all that \add is\add* in thine heart : turn thee; behold, I \add am\add* with thee according to thy heart.
Then said Jonathan , Behold, we will pass over unto \add these\add* men , and we will discover ourselves unto them.
If they say thus unto us, Tarry until we come to you; then we will stand still in our place, and will not go up unto them.\f + \fr 14.9 \ft Tarry: Heb. Be still\f*
But if they say thus, Come up unto us; then we will go up : for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath delivered them into our hand : and this \add shall be\add* a sign unto us.
And both of them discovered themselves unto the garrison of the Philistines : and the Philistines said , Behold, the Hebrews come forth out of the holes where they had hid themselves.

And the men of the garrison answered Jonathan and his armourbearer , and said , Come up to us, and we will shew you a thing. And Jonathan said unto his armourbearer , Come up after me: for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath delivered them into the hand of Israel.
And Jonathan climbed up upon his hands and upon his feet , and his armourbearer after him: and they fell before Jonathan ; and his armourbearer slew after him.

And that first slaughter , which Jonathan and his armourbearer made , was about twenty men , within as it were an half acre of land , \add which\add* a yoke \add of oxen might plow\add*.\f + \fr 14.14 \ft an…: or, half a furrow of an acre of land\f*

And there was trembling in the host , in the field , and among all the people : the garrison , and the spoilers , they also trembled , and the earth quaked : so it was a very great trembling.\f + \fr 14.15 \ft a very…: Heb. a trembling of God\f* \p
And the watchmen of Saul in Gibeah of Benjamin looked ; and, behold, the multitude melted away , and they went on beating down \add one another\add*.

Then said Saul unto the people that \add were\add* with him, Number now, and see who is gone from us. And when they had numbered , behold, Jonathan and his armourbearer \add were\add* not \add there\add*.
And Saul said unto Ahiah , Bring hither the ark of God. For the ark of God was at that time with the children of Israel. \p

¶ And it came to pass, while Saul talked unto the priest , that the noise that \add was\add* in the host of the Philistines went on and increased : and Saul said unto the priest , Withdraw thine hand.\f + \fr 14.19 \ft noise: or, tumult\f*

And Saul and all the people that \add were\add* with him assembled themselves, and they came to the battle : and, behold, every man’s sword was against his fellow , \add and there was\add* a very great discomfiture.\f + \fr 14.20 \ft assembled…: Heb. were cried together\f*

Moreover the Hebrews \add that\add* were with the Philistines before that time , which went up with them into the camp \add from the country\add* round about , even they also \add turned\add* to be with the Israelites that \add were\add* with Saul and Jonathan.
Likewise all the men of Israel which had hid themselves in mount Ephraim , \add when\add* they heard that the Philistines fled , even they also followed hard after them in the battle.
So the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* saved Israel that day : and the battle passed over unto Beth-aven. \p

¶ And the men of Israel were distressed that day : for Saul had adjured the people , saying , Cursed \add be\add* the man that eateth \add any\add* food until evening , that I may be avenged on mine enemies. So none of the people tasted \add any\add* food.
And all \add they of\add* the land came to a wood ; and there was honey upon the ground.
And when the people were come into the wood , behold, the honey dropped ; but no man put his hand to his mouth : for the people feared the oath.

But Jonathan heard not when his father charged the people with the oath : wherefore he put forth the end of the rod that \add was\add* in his hand , and dipped it in an honeycomb , and put his hand to his mouth ; and his eyes were enlightened.

Then answered one of the people , and said , Thy father straitly charged the people with an oath , saying , Cursed \add be\add* the man that eateth \add any\add* food this day. And the people were faint.\f + \fr 14.28 \ft faint: or, weary\f*
Then said Jonathan , My father hath troubled the land : see , I pray you, how mine eyes have been enlightened , because I tasted a little of this honey.
How much more , if haply the people had eaten freely to day of the spoil of their enemies which they found ? for had there not been now a much greater slaughter among the Philistines ?
And they smote the Philistines that day from Michmash to Aijalon : and the people were very faint.
And the people flew upon the spoil , and took sheep , and oxen , and calves , and slew \add them\add* on the ground : and the people did eat \add them\add* with the blood. \p

¶ Then they told Saul , saying , Behold, the people sin against the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, in that they eat with the blood. And he said , Ye have transgressed : roll a great stone unto me this day.\f + \fr 14.33 \ft transgressed: or, dealt treacherously\f*

And Saul said , Disperse yourselves among the people , and say unto them, Bring me hither every man his ox , and every man his sheep , and slay \add them\add* here, and eat ; and sin not against the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in eating with the blood. And all the people brought every man his ox with him that night , and slew \add them\add* there.\f + \fr 14.34 \ft with him: Heb. in his hand\f*

And Saul built an altar unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: the same was the first altar that he built unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.  +  r 14.35  t the same…: Heb. that altar he began to build unto the \+nd LORD\+nd* * \p

¶ And Saul said , Let us go down after the Philistines by night , and spoil them until the morning light , and let us not leave a man of them. And they said , Do whatsoever seemeth good unto thee. Then said the priest , Let us draw near hither unto God.
And Saul asked counsel of God , Shall I go down after the Philistines ? wilt thou deliver them into the hand of Israel ? But he answered him not that day.
And Saul said , Draw ye near hither , all the chief of the people : and know and see wherein this sin hath been this day.\f + \fr 14.38 \ft chief: Heb. corners\f*

For, \add as\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* liveth , which saveth Israel , though it be in Jonathan my son , he shall surely die. But \add there was\add* not a man among all the people \add that\add* answered him.
Then said he unto all Israel , Be ye on one side , and I and Jonathan my son will be on the other side. And the people said unto Saul , Do what seemeth good unto thee.

Therefore Saul said unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of Israel , Give a perfect \add lot\add*. And Saul and Jonathan were taken : but the people escaped.\f + \fr 14.41 \ft Give…: or, Shew the innocent\f*\f + \fr 14.41 \ft escaped: Heb. went forth\f*
And Saul said , Cast \add lots\add* between me and Jonathan my son. And Jonathan was taken.

Then Saul said to Jonathan , Tell me what thou hast done. And Jonathan told him, and said , I did but taste a little honey with the end of the rod that \add was\add* in mine hand , \add and\add*, lo , I must die.
And Saul answered , God do so and more also : for thou shalt surely die , Jonathan.

And the people said unto Saul , Shall Jonathan die , who hath wrought this great salvation in Israel ? God forbid : \add as\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* liveth , there shall not one hair of his head fall to the ground ; for he hath wrought with God this day. So the people rescued Jonathan , that he died not.
Then Saul went up from following the Philistines : and the Philistines went to their own place. \p

¶ So Saul took the kingdom over Israel , and fought against all his enemies on every side , against Moab , and against the children of Ammon , and against Edom , and against the kings of Zobah , and against the Philistines : and whithersoever he turned himself, he vexed \add them\add*.
And he gathered an host , and smote the Amalekites , and delivered Israel out of the hands of them that spoiled them.\f + \fr 14.48 \ft gathered…: or, wrought mightily\f*
Now the sons of Saul were Jonathan , and Ishui , and Melchi-shua : and the names of his two daughters \add were these;\add* the name of the firstborn Merab , and the name of the younger Michal :

And the name of Saul’s wife \add was\add* Ahinoam , the daughter of Ahimaaz : and the name of the captain of his host \add was\add* Abner , the son of Ner , Saul’s uncle.\f + \fr 14.50 \ft Abner: Heb. Abiner\f*
And Kish \add was\add* the father of Saul ; and Ner the father of Abner \add was\add* the son of Abiel.
And there was sore war against the Philistines all the days of Saul : and when Saul saw any strong man , or any valiant man , he took him unto him.
